4. Conclusions
The use of antifungals in agriculture has increased in recent years. Moreover, the recent rate
of emergence of fungicide-resistant pathogenic fungi has restricted the number of commonly used
antifungal agents. This has led to the need to develop new antifungal agents. However, research to
identify and characterize new antifungal drugs is challenging, and the discovery rate of new molecules
with antimicrobial potential is less than the emergence rate of new antifungal-resistant strains. Recently,
